summary:
Here is a clear and concise summary of the Security Council document:

The Security Council:

Recalling previous resolutions on Sierra Leone, 
Affirming commitment to respect Sierra Leone's sovereignty and territorial integrity,
Emphasizing continued international support for Sierra Leone's security and development,

 Extends UNAMSIL's mandate for a final 6-month period until 31 December 2005;
 Requests the Secretary-General to plan an integrated UN presence in Sierra Leone;
 Encourages close collaboration between UNAMSIL and the UN country team for a seamless transition;
 Recalls that Sierra Leone's security forces will assume full responsibility after UNAMSIL's withdrawal;
 Underlines the importance of providing security for the Special Court for Sierra Leone;
 Urges the Government of Sierra Leone to develop its security forces, police, and judiciary;
 Encourages inter-mission cooperation and implementation of disarmament programmes;
 Welcomes efforts to prevent sexual exploitation and abuse;
 Welcomes the Secretary-General's intention to monitor the situation and report regularly;
 Decides to remain seized of the matter.
